Global Smart Continuous Glucose Monitoring System Market Insights
Smart Continuous Glucose Monitoring System Market size was valued at USD 4.2 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 10.5 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 12.1% from 2024 to 2030.

Smart Continuous Glucose Monitoring System Market Overview
The global Smart Continuous Glucose Monitoring System (CGMS) market was valued at $2.30 billion in 2023 and is projected to reach $2.40 billion in 2024, with an estimated compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of 6.90%. By 2030, the market is expected to grow to $3.90 billion. This growth is driven by the increasing prevalence of diabetes worldwide and the growing awareness of the benefits of continuous glucose monitoring. Technological advancements, such as the development of new sensors, software, and smart algorithms, are making CGMS more accurate, user-friendly, and accessible. The integration of CGMS with insulin pumps and the use of telemedicine and remote monitoring are also contributing to market expansion. However, challenges such as the high cost of CGMS devices and the lack of reimbursement policies in many countries need to be addressed to fully realize the market's potential.

